Reasoning: The problem of converting a multigraph into a tree via vertex-breaking operations involves graph theory and computational complexity, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) the most likely categories. The paper also discusses planar graphs and hypergraphs, which could fall under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), respectively. Finally, the paper's focus on proving hardness suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a possible category.
